   Seats Sold at Stock Exchanges
</HL>
<DATE>
08/21/90
</DATE>
<SO>
WALL STREET JOURNAL (J), PAGE C13
</SO>
<IN>
STOCK MARKET, OFFERINGS (STK)
SECURITIES (SCR)
</IN>
<LP>
   NEW YORK -- The New York Stock Exchange said a seat was
sold for $310,000, down $10,000 from the previous sale last
Wednesday. Seats are currently quoted at $301,000, bid, and
$330,000, offered.
   Separately, the American Stock Exchange said a seat was
sold for $107,500, the lowest price since January 1980 and
down $10,000 from the last sale, on Aug. 3. Seats are being
quoted at $105,000, bid, and $115,000, offered.
</LP>
