BUYBACKS, REDEMPTIONS, SWAP OFFERS (BBK)
STOCK MARKET, OFFERINGS (STK)
</IN>
<LP>
   The following is a listing of securities called for
partial or complete redemption during the week ended Aug. 17,
1990. The notices are taken from advertisements appearing in
editions of The Wall Street Journal, and are not meant to be
definitive. Inquiries regarding specific issues should be
directed to the paying agent or, if none is listed, the
issuer.
                                                                                                       

                        MUNICIPALS
                                                                                                       

</LP>
<TEXT>
   FLORIDA HOUSING FINANCE AGENCY will call for redemption
$23,640,000 of its 1983 series H, FirstSouth Federal Savings
&amp; Loan Association, multifamily housing revenue bonds on
Sept. 1, 1990. Barnett Banks Trust Co., Miami, Fla., is
trustee.
   MISSOURI HOUSING DEVELOPMENT COMMISSION will redeem
$60,000 principal amount of its 9.625% housing development
bonds, Federally Insured Mortgage Loans, series Sept. 1,
1980, due Sept. 1, 2006, on Sept. 1, 1990. Mercantile Bank of
St. Louis is trustee.
                                                                                                       

                        CORPORATES
                                                                                                       

   BAKER HUGHES INC. will call for redemption on Aug. 31,
1990, its $3.50 convertible exchangeable preferred stock.
First Chicago Trust Co., New York, is the paying agent.
   TRANSCONTINENTAL GAS PIPE LINE CORP. will redeem its $2.50
cumulative preferred stock on Sept. 14, 1990. First Chicago
Trust Co., New York, is redemption agent.
</TEXT>
