<HL>
   Raw-Steel Production
   Increased Last Week
</HL>
<DATE>
08/21/90
</DATE>
<SO>
WALL STREET JOURNAL (J), PAGE C12
</SO>
<IN>
STEEL MANUFACTURERS (STL)
</IN>
<LP>
   WASHINGTON -- Raw-steel production by the nation's mills
increased 1.4% last week to 1,927,000 tons from 1,901,000
tons the previous week, the American Iron and Steel Institute
said.
   Last week's output rose 8.3% from the 1,779,000 tons
produced a year earlier.
</LP>
<TEXT>
   The industry used 86.4% of its capability last week,
compared with 85.2% the previous week and 79.9% a year
earlier.
                                                                                                       

   The American Iron and Steel Institute reported:
                                                                                                       

                                     Net tons   Capability
                                     produced   utilization
                                                                                                       

 Week to Aug. 18 ................   1,927,000       86.4
 Week to Aug. 11 ................   1,901,000       85.2
 Year to date ...................  62,290,000       87.2
 Year earlier to date ...........  63,962,000       87.6
                                                                                                       

   The capability utilization rate is a calculation designed
to indicate at what percent of its production capability the
industry is operating in a given week.
</TEXT>
