<HL>
   British Petroleum Co. Auction
</HL>
<DATE>
08/21/90
</DATE>
<SO>
WALL STREET JOURNAL (J), PAGE A11
</SO>
<CO>
   BP
</CO>
<IN>
TENDER OFFERS, MERGERS, ACQUISITIONS (TNM)
</IN>
<LP>
   LONDON (AP) -- British Petroleum Co. said it will auction
off its gas exploration and production holding company in the
Netherlands.
   BP refused to disclose the estimated value of BP
Exploratie B.V., a wholly owned subsidiary of British
Petroleum Nederland.
</LP>
<TEXT>
   The unit holds stakes in 23 offshore blocks and two
onshore, and analysts said the offer would fetch between $60
million and $70 million.
   The fields produce 14 million standard cubic feet of
natural gas each day, said a British Petroleum spokesman, who
spoke on condition of anonymity.
</TEXT>
