<HL>
   Varian Associates' Soviet Order
</HL>
<DATE>
08/21/90
</DATE>
<SO>
WALL STREET JOURNAL (J), NO PAGE CITATION
</SO>
<CO>
   VAR FREST
</CO>
<IN>
MONETARY NEWS, FOREIGN EXCHANGE, TRADE (MON)
</IN>
<LP>
   PALO ALTO, Calif. -- Varian Associates Inc. said it signed
"a multimillion dollar" pact with the Soviet Union to supply
cancer radiotherapy systems to several treatment centers.
   The order includes a range of cancer therapy equipment,
including linear accelerators to deliver precise doses of
radiation, radiotherapy simulators, therapy planning
computers and radiotherapy management systems.
</LP>
<TEXT>
   The first of the new systems was installed in early summer
at Moscow's All Union Oncology Center, the company said in a
news release. The other four cancer centers will receive
equipment next year, it said.
</TEXT>
